1
00:00:01,416 --> 00:00:02,750
[chorus vocalizing]

2
00:00:02,833 --> 00:00:03,541
RICARDO:<i> Hey, boy.</i>

3
00:00:03,625 --> 00:00:07,583
SUBARU:<i> No, this can't be.</i>

4
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:08,708
- What's wrong?

5
00:00:08,791 --> 00:00:10,791
- [chorus vocalizes]
- SUBARU: Huh?

6
00:00:10,875 --> 00:00:12,250
[gasps]

7
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:16,250
- [grunts]

8
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:18,375
- [wails]
- You spaced out,

9
00:00:18,458 --> 00:00:20,291
so I had to get your attention
somehow, neow, didn't I?

10
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:22,416
- Wait. Felix?

11
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,208
- Of course.
Who else do I look like?

12
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,458
Did you inhale too much
of the White Whale's fog?

13
00:00:26,541 --> 00:00:29,333
- Uh, no. I'm fine.

14
00:00:29,416 --> 00:00:31,375
Actually that told me
what I wanted to know.

15
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:33,583
<i>So this means...</i>

16
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:37,166
<i>my save point has been</i>
<i>updated to this moment?</i>

17
00:00:39,208 --> 00:00:40,166
- [chanting]

18
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:49,416
- ♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

19
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:53,291
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

20
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,125
[singing in Japanese]

21
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:39,500
♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

22
00:01:39,583 --> 00:01:42,583
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

23
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:44,708
[singing in Japanese]

24
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:50,250
♪ Grew up in the loneliness ♪

25
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:52,250
[singing in Japanese]

26
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:10,375
[wind blowing]

27
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:11,666
- There are a few new things

28
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:13,541
I've come to realize
about the Witch's Cult

29
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:14,583
that are definitely
worth mentioning.

30
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:16,625
LEADERS: Huh?

31
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:18,875
- Does anyone know
of something like...

32
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:20,375
a power you can use

33
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:21,291
to overwrite
someone's consciousness,

34
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:25,333
allowing you
to psychologically control them?

35
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:28,500
- In other words, you believe
that the Sin Archbishops

36
00:02:28,583 --> 00:02:29,375
may have such an ability?

37
00:02:29,458 --> 00:02:30,500
How unsettling.

38
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:31,875
- No kidding.

39
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:34,666
Somehow he's able
to possess others.

40
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:37,333
It's how he stays alive,

41
00:02:37,416 --> 00:02:38,708
and it would also explain

42
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:41,375
how he manages to keep
popping up everywhere.

43
00:02:41,458 --> 00:02:44,625
- Yes. I once saw an
account
of something quite similar

44
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:45,625
in an old book.

45
00:02:45,708 --> 00:02:47,375
It's a type of magic

46
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,250
that's been lost
over the centuries,

47
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,625
though it only works
under certain conditions.

48
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:51,583
- What do you mean?

49
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:54,833
- Few can use the method.

50
00:02:54,916 --> 00:02:58,458
It is said that certain select
members of the Witch's Cult

51
00:02:58,541 --> 00:02:59,916
acquired the capability.

52
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,291
- In that case,
I guess you mean the fingers?

53
00:03:02,375 --> 00:03:05,666
JULIUS: Most likely, they are
the user's spare bodies.

54
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,750
It's quite
a tasteless arrangement,

55
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,000
but beneficial
to a Sin Archbishop.

56
00:03:09,083 --> 00:03:12,375
- [gasps]
So if those confidants,

57
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:15,708
the fingers,
were to be wiped out...

58
00:03:15,791 --> 00:03:17,750
- Under that circumstance,

59
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:20,541
his soul would have
no vessel to take refuge in,

60
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:23,416
and that would be
the end of him, without a doubt.

61
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:23,916
- [gasps]

62
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,791
- We should eliminate

63
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:26,833
each of the fingers
in the forest first

64
00:03:26,916 --> 00:03:29,583
and then face Sloth directly.

65
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,000
That is my conclusion.

66
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:32,416
[Iron Fangs murmuring]

67
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,291
JULIUS: Hmm?

68
00:03:34,375 --> 00:03:36,291
- You guys,
there's one more thing

69
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:38,708
I need to say
about all this new info.

70
00:03:38,791 --> 00:03:42,458
Sorry, but I don't think
it's just the fingers.

71
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:44,958
Think he may have the capability
of possessing me, too.

72
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:49,708
So, uh, what do you
think I should do?

73
00:03:49,791 --> 00:03:50,791
- Huh?
- Huh?

74
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:53,958
-<i> Filthy woman.</i>

75
00:03:54,041 --> 00:03:56,416
<i>- Would you also</i>
<i>apologize for being born?</i>

76
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,791
<i>- You silver-haired half-elf.</i>

77
00:03:57,875 --> 00:04:00,708
<i>- A margrave maid has endorsed</i>
<i>a half-devil?</i>

78
00:04:00,791 --> 00:04:01,791
<i>- ...apologize for being born?</i>

79
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:03,000
<i>- I had such high hopes</i>
<i>for you.</i>

80
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:05,083
<i>- I thought maybe you...</i>
<i>- ...only you wouldn't give me</i>

81
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:08,041
<i>the special treatment that</i>
<i>surrounded me my entire life.</i>

82
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,250
<i>- Sorry. I can't do that.</i>
<i>- ...silver- haired half-elf.</i>

83
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,458
<i>- There's absolutely</i>
<i>no way I can look at you</i>

84
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:14,708
<i>the same way</i>
<i>I look at other people.</i>

85
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,250
<i>It's impossible.</i>

86
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:21,041
<i>- I've told you I'm not</i>
<i>connected to the Witch at all.</i>

87
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:23,125
[overlapping chatter]

88
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:30,500
[music playing]

89
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:31,500
- What's wrong?

90
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:34,000
Your forehead
looks all wrinkled.

91
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:35,500
- [chuckles]

92
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:37,708
Nothing. Good morning.

93
00:04:37,791 --> 00:04:39,500
You're starting
pretty early today.

94
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:40,750
- Good morning, Lia.

95
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,666
I figured I'd try going to sleep
and waking up earlier.

96
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:45,833
Ah, sorry. That was a lie.

97
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:46,791
The truth of the matter

98
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:49,833
is I've been kinda worried
about you lately.

99
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:52,958
You've had a rough go of it,
especially yesterday.

100
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:02,500
- It was nothing
I didn't know already.

101
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:03,625
- Even if you're sure
you'll fall down,

102
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:07,333
you still get hurt and bleed
when it happens, don't you?

103
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,708
- Tell me, Puck,

104
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:14,083
what do you think I should do?

105
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:17,500
I mean, what can I do
to be better to everybody?

106
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:22,541
And have them be better to me?

107
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:24,541
- [sighs]

108
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,458
Honestly, I think
you should do whatever you want.

109
00:05:27,541 --> 00:05:29,666
I'll be on your side,
no matter what.

110
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:31,125
Don't forget that, okay?

111
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:31,875
- [chuckles]

112
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:34,166
- Regardless of what you do,

113
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,916
you can't abandon everybody
in that village, right?

114
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,416
Ram went to go try again.

115
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,250
She headed out there
early this morning.

116
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:42,708
Maybe we should wait
to hear from her.

117
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,500
- [grunts]

118
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:49,625
- I think I'm gonna
check in on Betty.

119
00:05:49,708 --> 00:05:51,916
- Oh, okay. Sure.

120
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,458
Tell her hello for me.

121
00:05:56,041 --> 00:05:57,583
- [door closes]
- [gasps]

122
00:05:57,666 --> 00:05:59,708
Ram!

123
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:00,708
- Miss Emilia,

124
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:04,000
there's a visitor
who's come here to see you.

125
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:06,000
- I know you.

126
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:08,791
You're from Miss Crusch's
household, aren't you?

127
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,833
- My name is Wilhelm Trias.

128
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:16,125
I've come to speak with you
on behalf of my master.

129
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:18,125
- Is that so?

130
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:21,541
I received a blank letter
from her yesterday.

131
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:22,625
- Just as I feared, it's true.

132
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,666
- [gasps]

133
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:25,875
- I beg your pardon.

134
00:06:25,958 --> 00:06:28,708
While it shames me to say so,
the letter contradicted

135
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:30,875
the message
my master intended to send.

136
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:32,166
- Oh. It was a mistake, then?

137
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:37,625
- Yes. Miss Emilia,
and you, Miss Ram,

138
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:39,958
we would like to evacuate
those
remaining here in the mansion

139
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:42,875
as well as the nearby villagers.

140
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:44,916
That is Miss Crusch's will.

141
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,000
- Huh? Really?

142
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,750
There's a ring of criminals
near the forest?

143
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,458
RAM: Yes. The punitive force

144
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:53,125
this messenger
brought along with him

145
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,583
is already preparing
to fight the enemy as we speak.

146
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,625
- How kind.

147
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,708
But why would Miss Crusch
go out of her way

148
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,666
and do so much
to help this domain?

149
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,333
- My master received
a proposal from the margrave

150
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:08,708
to form an alliance with respect
to the royal selection.

151
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:10,833
The condition is a large share

152
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:13,000
of the mining rights
in Elior Forest.

153
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:14,916
Do you understand this, ma'am?

154
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,916
- Uh, so that's
what this is about.

155
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,166
- However, it will
certainly be difficult

156
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,333
to evacuate all the villagers
to the capital.

157
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:26,000
Our plan calls for roughly
half of them to go there.

158
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:28,375
- And as for the other half,

159
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:30,666
I will lead each one to safety
in the Sanctuary.

160
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:34,083
Lord Roswaal is heading there
now to make arrangements.

161
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:35,833
- Ah. Oh, I see.

162
00:07:35,916 --> 00:07:40,083
So discussion on the matter
is already over.

163
00:07:41,375 --> 00:07:42,541
I'm relieved.

164
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,916
But isn't this circumstance
a bit odd?

165
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,208
It seems too well timed.

166
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:46,875
[door slams open]

167
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:49,708
- Pardon me, sir!

168
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,041
The group hiding in the forest

169
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:51,750
has been observed
moving strangely.

170
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,875
- [gasps]

171
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:55,041
- We haven't a moment to waste
for the evacuation.

172
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:57,041
Once they make their move,

173
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:58,875
the whole region
will be a sea of blood!

174
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,958
What do you want us
to do, Captain?

175
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:03,875
No, Sword Demon Captain Wilhelm.

176
00:08:03,958 --> 00:08:05,875
- What is your decision?

177
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:08,125
- [sighs]

178
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:11,541
I understand,

179
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:15,500
and I gratefully
accept your kindness.

180
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:17,041
Has this been explained
to the villagers?

181
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,208
RAM: Yes. They've been informed

182
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,875
in a timely fashion,
Miss Emilia.

183
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,791
- I see.

184
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:25,291
- Betty says she'll stay here.

185
00:08:25,375 --> 00:08:26,333
- Puck!

186
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,083
<i>- Betty can't go</i>
<i>with you, I suppose.</i>

187
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:31,333
<i>I'll simply wait here</i>
<i>for you to return.</i>

188
00:08:31,416 --> 00:08:34,500
<i>There's no need</i>
<i>to worry about me.</i>

189
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,125
- So that's that.

190
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:38,750
Of course, in Betty's case,

191
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,208
the forbidden library
is a safer place to be anyway.

192
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,958
And besides, she can't
leave
the grounds of the mansion

193
00:08:44,041 --> 00:08:44,916
due to her contract.

194
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,750
You know that, right, Lia?

195
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:50,250
- She's using that
as a reason? Great.

196
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,375
- So since my cute little sister

197
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:54,416
will be staying here
and can look after things,

198
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,833
I don't think we should
do anything to the mansion.

199
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,208
Betty is kind and sweet,
of course,

200
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:00,583
but she'll show no mercy
to intruders.

201
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,208
- Understood, great spirit.

202
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:02,791
We shall heed your words.

203
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:05,291
- [grunts]

204
00:09:05,375 --> 00:09:06,333
- [gasps]

205
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:09,041
- Either way, you should do
whatever you wanna do.

206
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:11,666
Never forget what I told you.

207
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,666
I'm on your side,
and yours alone.

208
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:18,833
- We will evacuate.

209
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:20,666
The villagers need protection.

210
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,416
I don't want to put them
in any danger.

211
00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:25,083
- [chuckles]

212
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:32,125
- We're all packed up, Lady.

213
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:34,083
Ready when you are.

214
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:35,791
- Wait. What?

215
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:38,708
Sorry, but I think there
may have been a mistake.

216
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:41,041
- Not at all. Given the number
of people and carriages,

217
00:09:41,125 --> 00:09:43,291
to expedite the process,

218
00:09:43,375 --> 00:09:45,333
we ask you to share a ride
with these children.

219
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:48,083
It's a necessary measure.

220
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:50,166
- Can't we put them
in a different carriage?

221
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,750
Think that would be better,
for the children, that is.

222
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:55,875
- You think no one would want
to ride with you? Is that it?

223
00:09:55,958 --> 00:10:00,333
Tell me, have you asked the kids
how they feel about that?

224
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:02,666
Perhaps you just assumed
they hate you

225
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,083
and wouldn't want
to be around you

226
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:06,708
without any actual discussion
on the matter.

227
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:08,416
- No, that's not what I--

228
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,500
I don't need
to ask them to know.

229
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:13,791
I'm certain it would be best
for all of us.

230
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:15,833
- Six children
in one dragon-drawn carriage.

231
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:20,958
If we stumble here, how
will
your wish ever come true?

232
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,291
- Do I know you?

233
00:10:23,375 --> 00:10:26,333
- What do you think, Petra?

234
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:27,458
Do you have anything
against taking a ride

235
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:30,875
in the same carriage
as this lady here?

236
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:32,625
- [sighs]

237
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,791
- No, of course not.
- [gasps]

238
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:36,958
- I know her.

239
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:39,208
You're the lady with
the potato stamps, aren't you?

240
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:41,750
The same one who always
came along with Subaru

241
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:44,375
to watch when we'd do
our exercises.

242
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:45,791
- Well, I, uh...

243
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:48,208
- You didn't say much,
but I know it was you.

244
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:49,666
We couldn't see your face,

245
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,875
but we saw you having
a good time talking with him.

246
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:52,875
[giggles]

247
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:54,250
- [gasps]

248
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:56,791
- Please come and ride with us.

249
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,708
- [gasps]

250
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:00,250
- It'll be fun.

251
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:02,708
- Yeah, I wanna
ride with you, too.

252
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:04,833
- Come on. Let's go, already.

253
00:11:04,916 --> 00:11:05,958
- [children laughing]
- Let's go!

254
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:07,875
- Come with us.

255
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,916
- It's gonna be
pulled by a dragon!

256
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,291
- [children laughing]
- That's so cool!

257
00:11:13,375 --> 00:11:14,708
[Petra laughs]

258
00:11:14,791 --> 00:11:18,125
- Ram, take care of things
at the Sanctuary.

259
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:20,041
Be sure to protect
the villagers.

260
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:21,291
- Of course, Miss Emilia.

261
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,791
You take care as well.

262
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:23,708
- And, whoever you are,

263
00:11:23,791 --> 00:11:26,791
I'd like to thank you
for helping me to--

264
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:29,208
Huh? Where did he go?

265
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,250
- [sighs]

266
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:33,291
[wind blowing]

267
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:40,750
- SUBARU: Now I get it.
- Huh?

268
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,250
- We couldn't figure out
how you guys stayed in touch.

269
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,791
Those metia sure are handy,
aren't they?

270
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:46,833
- [blow strikes]
- Huh? [gasps]

271
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:49,375
- There's a heavy price to pay

272
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,333
for the crime of interrupting

273
00:11:51,416 --> 00:11:53,958
my touching and long-awaited
reunion with Emilia.

274
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,208
- [gasps] You're...

275
00:11:55,291 --> 00:11:56,791
[swords slash]

276
00:11:58,083 --> 00:11:59,041
- Too slow.

277
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:02,625
- [groans]

278
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:04,958
- Guess by now you've realized

279
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:06,458
we've had you pegged
as a spy for some time.

280
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:09,666
How we found out
is a little trade secret.

281
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:12,791
So knowing you were the contact
for the Witch's Cult,

282
00:12:12,875 --> 00:12:15,583
we laid out this trap
just for you.

283
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:17,333
Two hours.

284
00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:20,125
You gave your buddies
a schedule

285
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:22,708
that was two hours
behind the real time frame.

286
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:25,416
We can use that time to get
Emilia and the others out,

287
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:26,791
raid this forest,

288
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:29,291
and crush the fingers
that know our location,

289
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:31,000
then make
the proper preparations

290
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:33,958
to wipe out your Sin Archbishop
once and for all.

291
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:37,750
The feeling of your enemy
always being one step
ahead,

292
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:40,041
you're about to learn
just how terrifying it is

293
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:41,125
to be in that position.

294
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:43,916
[music playing]

295
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:47,708
- Please be careful.

296
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:50,083
May the blessings
of the spirits be with you.

297
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:56,333
- [gasps]

298
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:58,625
- May you prevail.

299
00:13:00,041 --> 00:13:01,583
- So this is what enabled you
to deceive Miss Emilia

300
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:03,333
and chase her
out of harm's way, huh?

301
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,833
- [groans] Come on!

302
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:06,958
Don't put it like that!

303
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:09,250
Even if it's accurate,
it makes me sound bad.

304
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:12,333
- That robe has been
woven
with quite a peculiar
spell.

305
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:14,958
- [sighs] It's a handmade item
by Roswaal.

306
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:17,041
Apparently there's
a spell laced into it

307
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:18,791
that prevents recognition.

308
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:20,041
Originally it was Emilia's,
but I--

309
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:21,833
[gasps]

310
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:23,916
Look, I didn't steal it, okay?!

311
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,958
- Sure.

312
00:13:26,041 --> 00:13:28,208
What a day, huh?

313
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:29,833
Things are looking up for you.

314
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:31,291
The mistake
with the blank letter,

315
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:32,416
correcting that worked out well.

316
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,875
RAM:<i> The letter was a mistake.</i>

317
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:42,125
<i>It was all my fault.</i>

318
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,416
- And all of those
doubtful villagers,

319
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,125
you worked hard
to convince them, Subaru.

320
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:48,125
- [gasps]

321
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:49,125
-<i> Please!</i>

322
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:51,416
<i>Emilia's--</i>

323
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:54,125
<i>she's a girl who could be</i>
<i>friends with every one of you,</i>

324
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:56,125
<i>and I want you</i>
<i>to give her the chance</i>

325
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:56,625
<i>to make you see that!</i>

326
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:58,375
[villagers murmuring]

327
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,708
<i>- I'm sure you all have</i>
<i>a lot you'd like to say,</i>

328
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:05,375
<i>but please let us</i>
<i>protect you long enough</i>

329
00:14:05,458 --> 00:14:07,083
<i>to allow that chance</i>
<i>to happen!</i>

330
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,500
- [sighs]

331
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:12,250
<i>Jeez.</i>

332
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,250
<i>You really are hopeless,</i>
<i>Subaru.</i>

333
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:15,250
<i>Get up, already.</i>

334
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,583
- [gasps]

335
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:21,541
<i>- If you insist</i>
<i>on protecting us so much,</i>

336
00:14:21,625 --> 00:14:24,333
<i>what choice do we have</i>
<i>in the matter?</i>

337
00:14:24,416 --> 00:14:25,833
<i>You've never let us down.</i>

338
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:28,416
<i>- Getting old</i>
<i>is the most awful thing.</i>

339
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:32,000
<i>My tear glands are weaker</i>
<i>than they once were.</i>

340
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,541
<i>- Thanks, everyone.</i>
<i>Thank you all.</i>

341
00:14:33,625 --> 00:14:36,458
<i>- We're the ones who should</i>
<i>be thanking you, young man.</i>

342
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:39,416
<i>We won't forget this.</i>

343
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,000
- Ah, you actually
moved me back there.

344
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:44,041
- Don't bring it up again!
It's embarrassing!

345
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:46,208
- [laughs] That just leaves...

346
00:14:47,291 --> 00:14:48,208
Welcome back!

347
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,041
How did it go?

348
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:52,125
- We all pulled off
the surprise attack

349
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:53,333
without a hitch.

350
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:54,416
That leaked intel
was as good as gold.

351
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:57,208
Your map helped out, too.

352
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:59,416
- Good to hear.
So the mark on the map

353
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:02,125
really was their base after all.
Lucky us.

354
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:05,291
- I don't know if you'd call
'em fastidious or high-strung,

355
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:06,000
but it worked against 'em.

356
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:09,291
And we got
what we were after, too.

357
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:11,625
This strike should shut down
the communications network.

358
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:15,291
- Hooray! We killed all of 'em!

359
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:18,166
- Please don't say that.
It makes us sound awful.

360
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:18,666
Oh, guess what!

361
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:20,750
We took a prisoner, too.

362
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,291
- A prisoner?

363
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:24,041
[boing, boing]

364
00:15:24,125 --> 00:15:26,000
- [groans]

365
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:27,583
SUBARU: [laughs] Nice!

366
00:15:27,666 --> 00:15:29,000
But he's not
in the Witch's Cult.

367
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:30,666
I was wondering
why you hadn't shown up yet.

368
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:34,333
You got caught, huh? [laughs]

369
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:36,500
- I don't know who you are,
and I don't care,

370
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:39,375
'cause either way, I'd like
to thank you for saving me.

371
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:41,166
Uh, what am I saying?!

372
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,375
I'm no mood
to claim that and mean it!

373
00:15:42,458 --> 00:15:45,125
- [laughing]
- Damn it!

374
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:49,666
[wind blowing]

375
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:52,000
JULIUS: Everything is
ready and accounted for.

376
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,166
Subaru, we can leave anytime.

377
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,208
- [grunts]

378
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:56,333
Let's do this, everyone.

379
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,791
We'll begin as planned.

380
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:00,708
Now...

381
00:16:00,791 --> 00:16:03,583
this time, we'll finish it!

382
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:06,166
Let's show Sloth and fate

383
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,166
what some motivated people
can do!

384
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:15,875
- [chorus vocalizing]
- I've been waiting to see you

385
00:16:15,958 --> 00:16:19,958
face to face for a long time,
believer in love.

386
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:22,458
I am a Sin Archbishop
of the Witch's Cult,

387
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:23,625
representing Sloth,

388
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:27,708
Betelgeuse Romanée-Conti, yes!

389
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:32,500
- It's a pleasure to meet you,
great Sin Archbishop.

390
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:35,458
If you could find it within you
to add my body and soul

391
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:38,166
to the ranks of your
fingers
carrying out the Ordeal,

392
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:39,083
there would be no greater honor.

393
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:43,750
- [whimpering]
- Please allow me into the fold.

394
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,291
- Oh, my!

395
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:49,291
How wondrous,
how vivacious your faith is.

396
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:52,250
[grunts] To think there was
such a devout believer.

397
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:55,083
Please forgive my sloth
for failing to find him!

398
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:55,625
- [pounding]
- Forgive me. Forgive me.

399
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:57,458
Forgive me. Forgive me.

400
00:16:57,541 --> 00:16:58,583
Forgive me! Forgive me!

401
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:01,125
- Please stop, Archbishop!
Don't!

402
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:02,250
- [winces]

403
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,708
But, but, but...

404
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,333
I have no way to atone

405
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:07,500
for the sloth and
foolishness I have shown

406
00:17:07,583 --> 00:17:09,500
but by self-inflicted
punishment.

407
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:11,750
- Look, that's not true,
and you know it.

408
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,791
The Witch wouldn't want
to see her beloved believer

409
00:17:13,875 --> 00:17:15,583
in such agony and pain.

410
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:17,375
She would be
much happier to see you

411
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:18,083
carry out the Ordeal
to completion!

412
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:21,166
- [gasps]
Now what was I thinking?

413
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:21,750
You are absolutely right.

414
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,791
Yes, of course. The Ordeal!

415
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:26,375
What she needs from me
right now is the Ordeal.

416
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:27,791
[yelps]

417
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:31,208
Your inspiring words
have opened my eyes.

418
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:33,166
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Uh...

419
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:36,625
- With this Ordeal,
we must test her

420
00:17:36,708 --> 00:17:39,625
and find out if this half-devil
is good enough,

421
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:43,125
if she is a worthy vessel
to put the Witch into.

422
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:45,250
- What are you talking about?

423
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:45,708
Worthy vessel?

424
00:17:45,791 --> 00:17:48,250
- If she is worthy,

425
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:49,083
the Witch will possess her.

426
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:52,250
If she is not,
the Witch will reject her.

427
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:56,250
If she proves a worthy vessel,
then the Witch will be reborn

428
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,208
into this world
on the coming fated day.

429
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:00,583
- Hang on a minute.

430
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:02,750
You're saying
Emilia is secondary,

431
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:05,541
with no value to you at all?

432
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:08,083
You monster.

433
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:11,333
- The words inscribed
on the pages of the Gospel

434
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:12,458
tell of her love!

435
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:14,666
All of it guides me
down this glorious path!

436
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:16,291
Time to show me your Gospel.

437
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:20,625
Eh? What's that?

438
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:22,708
- Just what it looks like,

439
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:25,458
a metia, Sin Archbishop.

440
00:18:26,541 --> 00:18:27,000
-<i> Huh?</i>

441
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:29,041
<i>I see him. I see him.</i>

442
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:32,458
<i>Ugh! His face looks</i>
<i>just as scary as I heard.</i>

443
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:33,583
- My face? Who are you?

444
00:18:33,666 --> 00:18:35,750
No! I mean what are you?!

445
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:38,541
-<i> Now then, Tora! Tora! Tora!</i>

446
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,291
[snap echoes]

447
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:41,333
- [roaring]

448
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,458
[groans]

449
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:46,291
- [roars]

450
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,916
- Looks like our surprise attack
is a success!

451
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,375
- What?!

452
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:52,750
[grumbles] Surprise attack?

453
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:56,416
Then what do you
think of this?!

454
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:59,250
- [warbling]

455
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,541
- How?!

456
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:03,708
How can your eyes
see my Authority?!

457
00:19:03,791 --> 00:19:05,416
- No idea.
Maybe you should ask the Witch

458
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:09,250
who left her scent all over me
for the answer to that
question.

459
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:10,583
Oh, that's right.

460
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:12,291
Unlike me, you haven't
received the special pass

461
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:15,875
letting you meet with the
Witch
anytime you want, have you?

462
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:19,125
- [gasps] What do you mean?
How dare you speak

463
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:20,416
as though you are intimate
with the Witch, imposter?!

464
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,708
- I'm not lying.

465
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:24,625
We're so close,
she's grabbed my heart...

466
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:25,666
literally.

467
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:28,041
- [stammers] Inconceivable!

468
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:28,541
[gags]

469
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:32,416
That simply cannot be!

470
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,500
- Come on! Let's go, Patrasche!

471
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:35,541
- [warbles]

472
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,458
[Authority moaning]

473
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:39,875
[warbles]

474
00:19:39,958 --> 00:19:42,875
- Don't you dare think
you can ever escape from me.

475
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,041
- Here he comes. Here he comes.

476
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:46,750
He's getting closer!

477
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,958
Hurry! Don't slow down!

478
00:19:49,875 --> 00:19:51,791
- [Authority warbles]
- Impossible!

479
00:19:51,875 --> 00:19:54,333
Vanish in the vengeful face
of my devoted diligence!

480
00:19:54,416 --> 00:19:57,416
[rumbling]

481
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,875
- [gasps]

482
00:19:58,958 --> 00:20:01,208
Sorry to rely on you
all the time.

483
00:20:01,291 --> 00:20:02,708
You're the greatest, Patrasche!

484
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,750
- But, but, but, but, but...

485
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:07,708
this is the end, the end!

486
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,666
- [gasps]

487
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,458
[both yell]

488
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,583
- [winces]

489
00:20:14,666 --> 00:20:15,375
Careful, you two.

490
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:18,208
You almost caught me up
in that blast.

491
00:20:18,291 --> 00:20:20,375
Thanks, though.
I thought I was a goner.

492
00:20:20,458 --> 00:20:22,583
- You're welcome, Subaru!
We're happy to help!

493
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:23,541
- Is that man
floating up in the sky

494
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:25,375
the Sin Archbishop?

495
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:28,916
MIMI: Whoa!
What the heck is that?

496
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,541
There's a balled-up man flying.
That's crazy!

497
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:34,291
- I never seen anything
look so creepy, seriously!

498
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:35,708
- So he just looks
like he's sitting down,

499
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:37,250
floating to you guys?

500
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:38,791
It doesn't matter.
Either way, leave him to me.

501
00:20:38,875 --> 00:20:41,666
Watch the rear like we planned!

502
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,666
- You got it, Subaru!

503
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:44,708
Let's do this, Sis.

504
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:47,208
- Aye, aye! Hey, bro,

505
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:49,791
