00:32:15,375 --> 00:32:17,000
- What's wrong?

764
00:32:17,083 --> 00:32:18,500
- Are you all right?

765
00:32:18,583 --> 00:32:20,583
- I'm sorry. It's nothing.

766
00:32:20,666 --> 00:32:22,666
Now come on.
We need to get going.

767
00:32:29,208 --> 00:32:30,625
- Damn it! Just when I think

768
00:32:30,708 --> 00:32:33,583
we've got it all under control,
everything backfires!

769
00:32:33,666 --> 00:32:36,375
- We verified that no spell
was used to set a trap,

770
00:32:36,458 --> 00:32:38,500
but if something were physically
rigged in the carriage,

771
00:32:38,583 --> 00:32:41,000
there's be no way of knowing
without seeing it.

772
00:32:41,083 --> 00:32:41,750
- Hey, Felix,
would a ground dragon

773
00:32:41,833 --> 00:32:44,708
be fast enough
to catch up with them?

774
00:32:44,791 --> 00:32:46,541
- If they're already
out of the Mathers domain

775
00:32:46,625 --> 00:32:48,041
and on the Lifaus Highway,

776
00:32:48,125 --> 00:32:50,250
then I think
it'd be pretty difficult.

777
00:32:50,333 --> 00:32:52,208
- That still wasn't enough?

778
00:32:52,291 --> 00:32:55,291
Even after everything we did,
I still can't...

779
00:32:55,375 --> 00:32:57,791
- Excuse me.
May I say something?

780
00:32:57,875 --> 00:33:00,750
I'm actually in a bit of
a desperate position right now.

781
00:33:00,833 --> 00:33:03,750
If you'd be willing
to accept a trade

782
00:33:03,833 --> 00:33:06,125
and help me out, I promise
to catch up to the carriage--

783
00:33:06,208 --> 00:33:09,625
If there's anything I can do
to make that happen, I'll do
it!

784
00:33:09,708 --> 00:33:12,333
- I like a man who can make
quick decisions, Mr. Natsuki.

785
00:33:12,416 --> 00:33:13,416
Thanks so much.

786
00:33:15,375 --> 00:33:18,208
- I'll send Ia along with you.
That should help.

787
00:33:18,291 --> 00:33:20,583
I wish I could
accompany you myself, but I...

788
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:21,500
- You can't, Julius.

789
00:33:21,583 --> 00:33:23,583
With all those injuries,

790
00:33:23,666 --> 00:33:25,458
what other help
could you possibly offer?

791
00:33:25,541 --> 00:33:27,458
And your mana's
not even restored yet.

792
00:33:27,541 --> 00:33:29,375
- You just get some rest, okay?

793
00:33:29,458 --> 00:33:31,208
Once this things finally over,
we can all celebrate.

794
00:33:31,291 --> 00:33:34,375
And I'll even make sure
to invite you, so don't die.

795
00:33:34,458 --> 00:33:36,458
- Don't you die, either.
Best of luck to you!

796
00:33:36,541 --> 00:33:38,208
- Careful out there.

797
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,708
OTTO: Instead of
taking this path,

798
00:33:41,791 --> 00:33:44,333
it's faster if we go off-road

799
00:33:44,416 --> 00:33:46,083
and cut through
the glade on the left.

800
00:33:46,166 --> 00:33:47,500
It's the shortest way!

801
00:33:49,375 --> 00:33:52,666
- Man, your soul of language
divine protection's amazing.

802
00:33:52,750 --> 00:33:55,583
- Thanks. I actually had a
hard
time learning to control it.

803
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:58,250
I can hear the voices
of all creatures, big and small,

804
00:33:58,333 --> 00:34:00,250
from ground dragons
to the tiniest of bugs.

805
00:34:00,333 --> 00:34:01,500
- Then if we choose our path

806
00:34:01,583 --> 00:34:02,458
based on all the
information
that they're giving you,

807
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,791
this shortcut will work,

808
00:34:04,875 --> 00:34:07,166
and catching up to Emilia
and the kids should be
easy.

809
00:34:07,250 --> 00:34:07,875
- What are you talking about?

810
00:34:07,958 --> 00:34:10,416
None of this
will be easy at all.

811
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:12,791
- [screaming]

812
00:34:15,875 --> 00:34:16,875
We're gonna die!

813
00:34:16,958 --> 00:34:19,750
We're seriously
gonna die at this rate!

814
00:34:19,833 --> 00:34:21,125
It's the end of the line!

815
00:34:21,208 --> 00:34:22,541
- What's this rush
washing over me?!

816
00:34:22,625 --> 00:34:24,250
I just feel so alive!

817
00:34:24,333 --> 00:34:27,166
Honestly, even I had no
idea
I was capable of doing--

818
00:34:27,250 --> 00:34:29,250
- [gasps]
- Hey, what's wrong?

819
00:34:29,333 --> 00:34:31,458
- What are you sensing?
- Something isn't right.

820
00:34:31,541 --> 00:34:33,041
The trees are getting so loud.

821
00:34:33,125 --> 00:34:34,458
The birds and bugs
started making a lot of noise

822
00:34:34,541 --> 00:34:37,291
and then vanished.

823
00:34:37,375 --> 00:34:40,666
There's something terrible
coming this way.

824
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:42,541
- [gasps]

825
00:34:42,625 --> 00:34:45,333
[music playing]

826
00:34:48,791 --> 00:34:50,541
Move it. Faster, Otto.

827
00:34:50,625 --> 00:34:52,166
Don't stop, no matter what!

828
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:53,416
- What are you doing?!

829
00:34:56,291 --> 00:34:58,708
- I should have known
that wasn't the end of you.

830
00:34:58,791 --> 00:34:59,583
Just how persistent
are you, damn it?!

831
00:34:59,666 --> 00:35:01,750
- My body! My flesh body!

832
00:35:01,833 --> 00:35:04,625
I must have it!
My head is trembling!

833
00:35:04,708 --> 00:35:07,541
[pants] Give it to me!

834
00:35:07,625 --> 00:35:08,250
[explosions]

835
00:35:11,791 --> 00:35:13,708
- [gasps]
- [children wail]

836
00:35:13,791 --> 00:35:16,208
- It's all right, everyone.
Just hang on tight.

837
00:35:16,291 --> 00:35:18,791
I'm sure there's nothing
to be afraid of, okay?

838
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:20,791
Huh?

839
00:35:20,875 --> 00:35:22,541
PUCK:<i> It would seem that old man</i>

840
00:35:22,625 --> 00:35:24,750
<i>just ran into</i>
<i>someone behind us.</i>

841
00:35:24,833 --> 00:35:26,333
<i>They're fighting.</i>

842
00:35:26,416 --> 00:35:27,625
EMILIA:<i> Do you know</i>
<i>how many there are?</i>

843
00:35:27,708 --> 00:35:29,666
<i>- Not exactly,</i>
<i>but there's a lot.</i>

844
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:33,125
<i>Have no fear.</i>
<i>The old man's power is no joke.</i>

845
00:35:33,208 --> 00:35:34,458
- [yelling]
- PUCK:<i> Looks like you and I</i>

846
00:35:34,541 --> 00:35:35,875
<i>won't be needed this time.</i>

847
00:35:35,958 --> 00:35:38,333
<i>Taking my physical form</i>
<i>without reason drains</i>
<i>mana,</i>

848
00:35:38,416 --> 00:35:40,333
<i>and I don't want to end up</i>
<i>being a plaything for the kids.</i>

849
00:35:40,416 --> 00:35:43,791
<i>- If your cuteness could help</i>
<i>everyone forget their fears,</i>

850
00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:46,541
<i>it might be worth it</i>
<i>to take that chance, Puck.</i>

851
00:35:46,625 --> 00:35:48,833
<i>- You sure say</i>
<i>some scary things, my daughter.</i>

852
00:35:50,041 --> 00:35:51,208
[children wail]

853
00:35:51,291 --> 00:35:52,125
- Now don't worry.

854
00:35:52,208 --> 00:35:53,583
Whatever happens,
I'll protect you.

855
00:35:53,666 --> 00:35:55,375
With me around,
there's nothing to fear.

856
00:35:55,458 --> 00:35:57,000
- W-We're okay! Seriously!

857
00:35:57,083 --> 00:35:58,541
- You don't have to worry
about us. We'll be all right.

858
00:35:58,625 --> 00:36:00,750
[children groan]

859
00:36:00,833 --> 00:36:03,375
- We made a promise,
so this is nothing!

860
00:36:03,458 --> 00:36:04,791
- What are you talking about?

861
00:36:04,875 --> 00:36:07,333
- That no matter what happens,
we wouldn't let go of you!

862
00:36:07,416 --> 00:36:08,708
- 'Cause if we're
not here beside you,

863
00:36:08,791 --> 00:36:10,291
you'll do something crazy.

864
00:36:10,375 --> 00:36:11,583
- And he'll be worried
if someone

865
00:36:11,666 --> 00:36:13,250
isn't watching you
this whole trip!

866
00:36:13,333 --> 00:36:15,625
- Who made such a fuss about me?

867
00:36:15,708 --> 00:36:16,916
Why are they so concerned?

868
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,708
- Don't! We can't tell her!

869
00:36:18,791 --> 00:36:21,250
- Subaru!
- He asked us for a favor, okay?

870
00:36:21,333 --> 00:36:23,750
He said you get lonely,
so he was worried about you.

871
00:36:23,833 --> 00:36:25,750
- Yeah! He said--Wait.

872
00:36:25,833 --> 00:36:28,416
I don't think we were
supposed to tell her about that.

873
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:29,875
- Oh, no.

874
00:36:29,958 --> 00:36:32,666
- [gasps]

875
00:36:32,750 --> 00:36:36,250
- [trees creaking]
- Mr. Natsuki, what is it?

876
00:36:36,333 --> 00:36:36,875
Is there something behind us?

877
00:36:36,958 --> 00:36:37,916
- Just some big, black animal

878
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,916
with a bunch of legs
and a bad attitude.

879
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:42,041
It has a wild voice
and a scary face,

880
00:36:42,125 --> 00:36:44,375
so you're better off
not looking.

881
00:36:44,458 --> 00:36:45,666
- Everything you're saying
just makes me

882
00:36:45,750 --> 00:36:47,375
want to take a look even more!

883
00:36:47,458 --> 00:36:49,041
- Keep your curiosity in check,
and keep driving!

884
00:36:49,125 --> 00:36:51,458
If it takes a bite out of me,
you're gonna be next!

885
00:36:51,541 --> 00:36:52,458
- [wails]

886
00:36:52,541 --> 00:36:54,291
- Hmph.

887
00:36:54,375 --> 00:36:56,791
How many times do I
have to play the last level?

888
00:36:56,875 --> 00:36:58,625
What about you
is slothful now?

889
00:36:58,708 --> 00:37:00,458
Looks like you're working
pretty hard to me.

890
00:37:00,541 --> 00:37:01,708
- Give me the Witch!

891
00:37:01,791 --> 00:37:03,458
Give me Satella!
Give her to me!

892
00:37:03,541 --> 00:37:04,791
- Give me love, love...
- Listen!

893
00:37:04,875 --> 00:37:06,791
She doesn't love you
or me, you idiot!

894
00:37:06,875 --> 00:37:08,166
What kind of rom-com

895
00:37:08,250 --> 00:37:09,875
has someone trying to squash
their love's heart!

896
00:37:09,958 --> 00:37:12,625
- Satella! Satella!
Satella! Satella!

897
00:37:12,708 --> 00:37:14,625
- I'm the one
who stands before you.

898
00:37:14,708 --> 00:37:16,666
As your opponent,
I won't let you get past me,

899
00:37:16,750 --> 00:37:19,625
and I absolutely won't let you
get to the kid in front of me,

900
00:37:19,708 --> 00:37:20,916
you insane, evil bastard!

901
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,291
- Oh, that's so touching.

902
00:37:22,375 --> 00:37:23,708
You care about me that much,
Mr. Natsuki?

903
00:37:23,791 --> 00:37:24,666
- Will you be quiet, already?!

904
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:27,375
I'm trying to make myself
look good back here!

905
00:37:27,458 --> 00:37:28,833
[Authority moaning]

906
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:34,541
- [yells]

907
00:37:34,625 --> 00:37:35,166
- Look, Mr. Natsuki!

908
00:37:35,250 --> 00:37:37,083
We're leaving the forest!

909
00:37:39,708 --> 00:37:41,916
[music playing]

910
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,000
- Love. Love me. Love me.

911
00:37:45,083 --> 00:37:48,250
Love alone is everything.
Love alone!

912
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:49,875
- If you think I'm gonna
take you where Emilia is,

913
00:37:49,958 --> 00:37:51,750
you've got another think coming!

914
00:37:51,833 --> 00:37:53,916
[Subaru grunts]

915
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,708
- [growls]

916
00:37:55,791 --> 00:37:57,916
[Authority moaning]

917
00:37:58,916 --> 00:38:01,791
- One last card to play.

918
00:38:01,875 --> 00:38:04,750
Thanks for your strength
and help, Julius.

919
00:38:04,833 --> 00:38:08,291
How 'bout a little rental<i> Goa?!</i>

920
00:38:11,750 --> 00:38:12,666
[groans]

921
00:38:14,791 --> 00:38:16,583
Damn it! That hurts!

922
00:38:16,666 --> 00:38:18,666
Man. [gasps]

923
00:38:18,750 --> 00:38:20,041
- Give it to me!

924
00:38:20,125 --> 00:38:22,333
Hand it over! Relinquish it!

925
00:38:22,416 --> 00:38:24,708
- I told you,
if you try to get into my body,

926
00:38:24,791 --> 00:38:25,750
you're only gonna get hurt!

927
00:38:25,833 --> 00:38:27,041
The Witch doesn't
want to see you!

928
00:38:27,125 --> 00:38:31,875
- The Witch! Satella! Satella!

929
00:38:31,958 --> 00:38:33,708
I haven't forgotten
a single moment

930
00:38:33,791 --> 00:38:35,416
of the things you did for me!

931
00:38:35,500 --> 00:38:36,041
I'll treasure them forever!

932
00:38:36,125 --> 00:38:38,875
Even if you've forgotten,

933
00:38:38,958 --> 00:38:41,875
your humble servant
will always remember!

934
00:38:41,958 --> 00:38:43,666
With all of my diligence,

935
00:38:43,750 --> 00:38:45,958
- I'll part with my slothful...
- Bad call, man.

936
00:38:46,041 --> 00:38:47,333
Sucks for you.

937
00:38:47,416 --> 00:38:49,541
Who knows?
If you'd stayed a monster,

938
00:38:49,625 --> 00:38:50,833
you might have beaten me!

939
00:38:53,125 --> 00:38:54,666
- [gasps]

940
00:38:54,750 --> 00:38:56,375
Satella.

941
00:38:57,708 --> 00:38:59,583
[wind howling]

942
00:39:00,833 --> 00:39:01,583
- [yells]

943
00:39:01,666 --> 00:39:05,125
- [gags]

944
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:11,041
I will not--I won't let it end.

945
00:39:11,125 --> 00:39:12,833
This hasn't ended.

946
00:39:12,916 --> 00:39:14,458
[coughs] It hasn't.

947
00:39:14,541 --> 00:39:16,916
[groans]

948
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:17,833
- No, you're wrong.

949
00:39:17,916 --> 00:39:20,458
It's finally over.

950
00:39:20,541 --> 00:39:22,500
As of now, you're finished!

951
00:39:22,583 --> 00:39:24,750
- [gasps]

952
00:39:25,833 --> 00:39:27,041
[growls]

953
00:39:33,791 --> 00:39:38,750
Subaru Natsuki!

954
00:39:38,833 --> 00:39:41,000
[wails]

955
00:39:43,250 --> 00:39:45,125
- [sighs]

956
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:49,000
And this time,
stay asleep forever, Betelgeuse.

957
00:39:49,083 --> 00:39:50,958
Don't ever come back.

958
00:39:51,041 --> 00:39:51,791
- Hey, up ahead!

959
00:39:51,875 --> 00:39:53,833
- [gasps]

960
00:39:58,583 --> 00:40:00,666
Wilhelm!

961
00:40:00,750 --> 00:40:02,625
- Subaru, son.

962
00:40:02,708 --> 00:40:04,000
- Where's Emilia?!

963
00:40:08,791 --> 00:40:10,958
- She's that way!

964
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:13,083
Go straight
toward the great tree!

965
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:17,958
This is the perfect chance
to repay my debt!

966
00:40:18,041 --> 00:40:19,916
I pity anyone
who stands in the path

967
00:40:20,041 --> 00:40:22,500
of a man
who's on his way to see a woman!

968
00:40:25,291 --> 00:40:26,750
[chorus vocalizing]

969
00:40:27,916 --> 00:40:29,916
- [gasps] R-Right there.

970
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,041
I see it, the carriage
with the refugees.

971
00:40:33,125 --> 00:40:34,791
[no audible dialogue]

972
00:40:41,750 --> 00:40:45,166
SUBARU: Back then,
I made a promise.

973
00:40:49,750 --> 00:40:52,125
I swore, no matter what...

974
00:40:53,666 --> 00:40:55,583
I would risk everything
to try and save you.

975
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,875
PUCK:<i> So are you</i>
<i>thinking about Subaru?</i>

976
00:41:03,958 --> 00:41:05,041
EMILIA:<i> Yeah.</i>

977
00:41:05,125 --> 00:41:06,541
<i>But it's crazy.</i>

978
00:41:06,625 --> 00:41:07,541
<i>I still can't believe it.</i>

979
00:41:07,625 --> 00:41:11,041
-<i> I can. If he's</i>
<i>really leading the army,</i>

980
00:41:11,125 --> 00:41:12,875
<i>a lot of things</i>
<i>would make sense,</i>

981
00:41:12,958 --> 00:41:14,583
<i>like why Ram didn't argue</i>

982
00:41:14,666 --> 00:41:16,541
<i>and why the villagers</i>
<i>agreed to evacuate</i>

983
00:41:16,625 --> 00:41:18,083
<i>without putting up</i>
<i>any resistance.</i>

984
00:41:18,166 --> 00:41:20,041
-<i> But still...</i>

985
00:41:20,125 --> 00:41:21,458
<i>why?</i>

986
00:41:21,541 --> 00:41:23,583
<i>After all the pain and</i>
<i>suffering he went through...</i>

987
00:41:25,083 --> 00:41:27,083
<i>after I made him look so sad...</i>

988
00:41:28,791 --> 00:41:30,208
<i>why would he...</i>

989
00:41:30,291 --> 00:41:31,291
- [carriage rattles]
- [gasps]

990
00:41:31,375 --> 00:41:32,541
[children moan]

991
00:41:32,625 --> 00:41:34,125
<i>- Lia, something's</i>
<i>coming up behind us.</i>

992
00:41:34,208 --> 00:41:35,166
- [roars]

993
00:41:37,958 --> 00:41:39,708
[all gasp]

994
00:41:52,875 --> 00:41:54,000
- [gasps]

995
00:41:55,958 --> 00:41:57,750
- [gasps]

996
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:00,958
[gasps]

997
00:42:07,208 --> 00:42:09,583
- [stones pulse]
- There. Found them.

998
00:42:09,666 --> 00:42:12,875
- I thought a reunion like this
seemed a little sudden for you.

999
00:42:12,958 --> 00:42:14,125
So that's why you're here, huh?

1000
00:42:14,208 --> 00:42:16,625
[singer vocalizing]

1001
00:42:16,708 --> 00:42:17,041
- [grunts]

1002
00:42:17,125 --> 00:42:17,916
- Wait a minute!

1003
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,041
You shouldn't...

1004
00:42:26,208 --> 00:42:27,708
Why, Subaru?

1005
00:42:29,375 --> 00:42:32,666
- 'Cause I love you, Emilia.

1006
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:35,125
- [gasps] Eh?

1007
00:42:35,208 --> 00:42:37,166
[music playing]

1008
00:42:46,083 --> 00:42:48,958
[singing in Japanese]

1009
00:42:52,875 --> 00:42:54,791
- Damn it!

1010
00:42:54,875 --> 00:42:57,833
Get there in time!

1011
00:43:00,833 --> 00:43:01,958
[stones pulse]

1012
00:43:02,041 --> 00:43:03,583
[singing continues]

1013
00:43:11,208 --> 00:43:12,291
-<i> An easy price to pay.</i>

1014
00:43:12,375 --> 00:43:15,416
<i>Thanks for saving me, Subaru.</i>

1015
00:43:19,750 --> 00:43:26,041
- ♪ I stay alive ♪

1016
00:43:26,125 --> 00:43:28,000
[singing in Japanese]

1017
00:43:28,083 --> 00:43:29,041
- [gasps]

1018
00:43:34,125 --> 00:43:35,625
[singing continues]

1019
00:43:39,958 --> 00:43:41,000
SUBARU:<i> Where am I?</i>

1020
00:43:41,083 --> 00:43:44,166
<i>I can't see a thing.</i>

1021
00:43:44,250 --> 00:43:46,625
<i>I can't hear a thing.</i>

1022
00:43:46,708 --> 00:43:50,083
<i>Is that Witch lady coming</i>
<i>to grab my heart again?</i>

1023
00:43:50,166 --> 00:43:50,791
<i>Who knows?</i>

1024
00:43:50,875 --> 00:43:53,166
<i>I don't feel too bad, though.</i>

1025
00:43:53,250 --> 00:43:56,875
EMILIA: Subaru! Subaru!

1026
00:43:56,958 --> 00:44:00,083
<i>- Oh, hey.</i>
<i>I can hear after all.</i>

1027
00:44:00,916 --> 00:44:01,875
[song ends]

1028
00:44:01,958 --> 00:44:05,291
[rumbling]

1029
00:44:05,375 --> 00:44:07,250
- [gasping]

1030
00:44:07,333 --> 00:44:07,916
[roar echoes]

1031
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,250
[gasps]

1032
00:44:10,333 --> 00:44:12,750
[footsteps pattering]

1033
00:44:12,833 --> 00:44:13,791
[panting]

1034
00:44:23,458 --> 00:44:24,750
- [groans]

1035
00:44:26,333 --> 00:44:28,000
- [sighs]

1036
00:44:28,083 --> 00:44:30,208
[gasps]

1037
00:44:30,291 --> 00:44:31,416
[cries]

1038
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:34,125
Subaru!

1039
00:44:40,458 --> 00:44:42,000
[wind blowing]

1040
00:44:42,083 --> 00:44:44,250
[music playing]

1041
00:44:53,875 --> 00:44:54,500
- [groans]

1042
00:44:54,583 --> 00:44:58,083
- Subaru, you're finally awake.

1043
00:44:58,166 --> 00:45:00,250
Thank goodness. I'm so glad.

1044
00:45:00,333 --> 00:45:02,458
- I-I'm laying down.

1045
00:45:02,541 --> 00:45:03,375
And Mili's kneeling.

1046
00:45:03,458 --> 00:45:06,875
Hold on.
I need to get my bearings here.

1047
00:45:06,958 --> 00:45:08,083
Considering my perspective,

1048
00:45:08,166 --> 00:45:10,750
our distance from each other,
and the heavenly sensation

1049
00:45:10,833 --> 00:45:12,125
that's under my head,
could it be...

1050
00:45:12,208 --> 00:45:14,958
- You don't have to go
through all that, silly.

1051
00:45:15,041 --> 00:45:16,291
Your head's on my lap.

1052
00:45:16,375 --> 00:45:18,041
It's not too uncomfortable,
is it?

1053
00:45:18,125 --> 00:45:20,041
- There's no finer,
more divine pillow

1054
00:45:20,125 --> 00:45:21,041
I could possibly imagine.

1055
00:45:21,125 --> 00:45:23,458
- [chuckles]

1056
00:45:23,541 --> 00:45:24,458
- Hey, um...

1057
00:45:24,541 --> 00:45:25,416
would it be okay

1058
00:45:25,500 --> 00:45:28,208
if you told me
how things turned out?

1059
00:45:28,291 --> 00:45:30,250
- Well...

1060
00:45:30,333 --> 00:45:31,666
to be perfectly honest,

1061
00:45:31,750 --> 00:45:33,958
I'm the one who wants to ask
what's going on.

1062
00:45:34,041 --> 00:45:36,375
- Is Patrasche all right?

1063
00:45:36,458 --> 00:45:39,708
I want to become the wind
with that critter again.

1064
00:45:39,791 --> 00:45:41,375
- She was pretty badly burned,
but she's strong.

1065
00:45:41,458 --> 00:45:44,125
I think she'll be fine.

1066
00:45:44,208 --> 00:45:46,083
Felix is looking after her.

1067
00:45:46,166 --> 00:45:47,083
- Oh. Felix joined us, too?

1068
00:45:47,166 --> 00:45:49,416
Wow. [chuckles]

1069
00:45:49,500 --> 00:45:51,958
So have I been out
for a long time?

1070
00:45:52,041 --> 00:45:53,208
- Mm...

1071
00:45:53,291 --> 00:45:54,916
about an hour or two.

1072
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:57,291
- Then I guess
everybody's together now.

1073
00:45:57,375 --> 00:46:00,416
- Julius, too. [chuckles]

1074
00:46:00,500 --> 00:46:01,541
Even him.

1075
00:46:01,625 --> 00:46:03,333
I was really surprised.

1076
00:46:03,416 --> 00:46:06,000
I never expected to see
you two getting along,

1077
00:46:06,083 --> 00:46:07,375
much less working together.

1078
00:46:07,458 --> 00:46:10,166
- It was
for the very best of reasons,

1079
00:46:10,250 --> 00:46:12,000
ones bluer than the mountains,
taller than the seas,

1080
00:46:12,083 --> 00:46:14,041
dear Mili.

1081
00:46:18,125 --> 00:46:20,500
[Mimi groans]

1082
00:46:20,583 --> 00:46:21,958
[veteran sighs]

1083
00:46:23,625 --> 00:46:24,500
- Finally.

1084
00:46:24,583 --> 00:46:27,166
I finally made it
all the way back.

1085
00:46:28,416 --> 00:46:31,916
Feels like I was having
a really long dream,

1086
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:33,083
a terrible one.

1087
00:46:33,166 --> 00:46:35,875
Maybe not that bad.

1088
00:46:35,958 --> 00:46:38,166
- Then it was a good dream?

1089
00:46:39,458 --> 00:46:41,500
- More like a good reality.

1090
00:46:41,583 --> 00:46:43,333
- Hmm?

1091
00:46:43,416 --> 00:46:45,125
- Back then, you asked me

1092
00:46:45,208 --> 00:46:47,875
why I was doing all the things
I was doing,

1093
00:46:47,958 --> 00:46:49,916
why I desperately
tried to save you,

1094
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,166
and why I always seemed
to put in so much effort.

1095
00:46:52,250 --> 00:46:55,083
You asked me why.

1096
00:46:55,166 --> 00:46:56,375
- [sighs]

1097
00:46:56,458 --> 00:46:57,666
- Your answer confused me.

1098
00:46:57,750 --> 00:47:00,958
You said that it
was because I saved you,

1099
00:47:01,041 --> 00:47:06,000
but I-I haven't done
anything like that at all.

1100
00:47:06,083 --> 00:47:08,166
I've never been able to.

1101
00:47:08,250 --> 00:47:11,375
It seems like you're the one
who's always saving me.

1102
00:47:11,458 --> 00:47:13,958
I could never
do anything for you.

1103
00:47:14,041 --> 00:47:18,000
And every time, you'd get hurt
and say that it was for my
sake.

1104
00:47:18,083 --> 00:47:20,125
- No, I was
pretty messed up back then.

1105
00:47:20,208 --> 00:47:21,916
[sighs]

1106
00:47:22,666 --> 00:47:25,250
I was only thinking
about myself.

1107
00:47:25,333 --> 00:47:27,708
I said it was all for you,

1108
00:47:27,791 --> 00:47:31,000
but I really just liked the idea
of doing it all for you.

1109
00:47:31,083 --> 00:47:34,583
I had it in my head that if
I just kept telling you that,

1110
00:47:34,666 --> 00:47:36,458
you'd accept it.

1111
00:47:36,541 --> 00:47:38,333
- Subaru

1112
00:47:38,416 --> 00:47:39,916
- I'm sorry.

1113
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:43,166
I used you for my own
stupid self-satisfaction.

1114
00:47:43,250 --> 00:47:45,208
All the things you said
back then were true,

1115
00:47:45,291 --> 00:47:47,458
every word of it.

1116
00:47:47,541 --> 00:47:48,666
I was just so wrong.

1117
00:47:48,750 --> 00:47:53,958
But there's one thing
I wasn't wrong about.

1118
00:47:54,041 --> 00:47:56,250
I want to save you.

1119
00:47:56,333 --> 00:47:58,166
I want to help you.

1120
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:00,125
I honestly mean that.

1121
00:48:00,208 --> 00:48:01,166
It's not a lie.

1122
00:48:01,250 --> 00:48:03,291
- [sighs]

1123
00:48:03,375 --> 00:48:05,125
I know that.

1124
00:48:06,708 --> 00:48:10,958
Tell me, why do you
always rescue me?

1125
00:48:13,375 --> 00:48:14,708
- I do it because I love you.

1126
00:48:14,791 --> 00:48:18,333
I want to stand beside you
and be your strength.

1127
00:48:20,708 --> 00:48:22,041
- [cries]

1128
00:48:26,541 --> 00:48:29,000
Listen. I'm a half-elf.

1129
00:48:29,083 --> 00:48:29,708
- Yes, I know that.

1130
00:48:29,791 --> 00:48:32,416
- I'm a silver-haired half-elf,

1131
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:34,916
and people,
so many people hate me

1132
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:37,291
for no other reason than
because I look like the Witch.

1133
00:48:37,375 --> 00:48:39,375
They despise me.

1134
00:48:39,458 --> 00:48:42,250
They absolutely detest me!

1135
00:48:42,333 --> 00:48:43,583
- I saw. I know.

1136
00:48:43,666 --> 00:48:45,916
Those guys are completely blind.

1137
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:48,666
- I don't have much experience
with people,

1138
00:48:48,750 --> 00:48:50,500
so I don't have friends.

1139
00:48:50,583 --> 00:48:52,166
I'm naive and not worldly,

1140
00:48:52,250 --> 00:48:54,833
so I say strange things
sometimes.

1141
00:48:54,916 --> 00:48:56,500
And the reason I want to be
the ruler of this kingdom

1142
00:48:56,583 --> 00:48:59,583
is really, really selfish.

1143
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:03,166
- No matter what anyone else
says about you,

1144
00:49:03,250 --> 00:49:04,625
no matter what you
happen to think of yourself,

1145
00:49:04,708 --> 00:49:06,625
I love you with all my heart.

1146
00:49:06,708 --> 00:49:09,625
I mean it! I'm crazy about you!

1147
00:49:09,708 --> 00:49:12,041
I want to be with you
all the time.

1148
00:49:12,125 --> 00:49:14,000
I want to hold your hand
all the time.

1149
00:49:14,083 --> 00:49:16,166
You could sit there
and come up with a list

1150
00:49:16,250 --> 00:49:17,666
of ten things
you hate about yourself,

1151
00:49:17,750 --> 00:49:19,083
but I'd just reply

1152
00:49:19,166 --> 00:49:21,375
with 2,000 things
that I love about you.

1153
00:49:22,625 --> 00:49:23,541
That's the kind
of special treatment

1154
00:49:23,625 --> 00:49:25,541
I want to give you.

1155
00:49:27,250 --> 00:49:29,833
That's the depth
of the love in my heart.

1156
00:49:31,916 --> 00:49:34,208
- You know,
that's the first time

1157
00:49:34,291 --> 00:49:37,125
I've received special
treatment
that actually made me happy.

1158
00:49:37,208 --> 00:49:39,208
[cries]

1159
00:49:39,291 --> 00:49:41,333
[gasps]

1160
00:49:42,791 --> 00:49:43,375
I don't get it.

1161
00:49:43,458 --> 00:49:44,833
Why 2,000?

1162
00:49:44,916 --> 00:49:48,458
- Because a hundredfold
just isn't enough,

1163
00:49:48,541 --> 00:49:50,625
doesn't come close
to how I feel about you.

1164
00:49:51,291 --> 00:49:53,000
I'm happy...

1165
00:49:54,291 --> 00:49:55,708
just so very happy.

1166
00:49:56,791 --> 00:49:58,541
I never even dared to dream

1167
00:49:58,625 --> 00:49:59,791
that a day like this
would happen,

1168
00:49:59,875 --> 00:50:03,541
when someone
would tell me they loved me.

1169
00:50:03,625 --> 00:50:05,291
What should I do?

1170
00:50:05,375 --> 00:50:06,833
What do I say?

1171
00:50:06,916 --> 00:50:09,708
You've told me so many
of your thoughts and feelings.

1172
00:50:09,791 --> 00:50:12,541
I'm thankful,
but also a little overwhelmed.

1173
00:50:12,625 --> 00:50:14,750
I don't know what I'm supposed
to do at a time like this.

1174
00:50:14,833 --> 00:50:16,875
You don't have
to stress over it.

1175
00:50:16,958 --> 00:50:19,583
I'm not demanding
an answer right away.

1176
00:50:19,666 --> 00:50:22,250
The way I see it is this.

1177
00:50:22,333 --> 00:50:23,250
I'll get your answer one day,

1178
00:50:23,333 --> 00:50:26,291
and I'm confident
of what that answer will be.

1179
00:50:26,375 --> 00:50:27,583
- Really? I mean...

1180
00:50:27,666 --> 00:50:31,750
is it okay for someone like me

1181
00:50:31,833 --> 00:50:35,083
to be given such pure happiness
all the time?

1182
00:50:35,166 --> 00:50:37,583
To know such joy
in my heart that it--

1183
00:50:37,666 --> 00:50:39,458
it actually feels
beyond indulgent?

1184
00:50:39,541 --> 00:50:41,666
- Sure it is.
Go on and be indulgent.

1185
00:50:41,750 --> 00:50:44,125
As far as I'm concerned,

1186
00:50:44,208 --> 00:50:46,083
you can never have
too much happiness.

1187
00:50:46,166 --> 00:50:47,791
If there's so much,
it overflows,

1188
00:50:47,875 --> 00:50:49,333
you can share it, you know?

1189
00:50:49,416 --> 00:50:51,291
- [gasps]

1190
00:50:51,375 --> 00:50:52,833
- Don't worry.

1191
00:50:52,916 --> 00:50:54,750
Take your time, Emilia.

1192
00:50:54,833 --> 00:50:57,750
Take as much as you need.

1193
00:50:57,833 --> 00:51:01,125
Then, little by little,
you'll fall in love, too.

1194
00:51:01,208 --> 00:51:03,291
I'll always be there
at your side.

1195
00:51:03,375 --> 00:51:04,125
That way,
I'll be sure to catch you

1196
00:51:04,208 --> 00:51:06,625
when you fall
head over heels for me.

1197
00:51:06,708 --> 00:51:07,750
- [music playing]
- ♪ I wish I was there ♪

1198
00:51:07,833 --> 00:51:10,375
♪ Oh, please don't
let me die... ♪

1199
00:51:10,458 --> 00:51:12,500
- [crying]

1200
00:51:12,583 --> 00:51:14,583
- [singing in Japanese]

1201
00:51:16,708 --> 00:51:18,791
- Thank you, Subaru...

1202
00:51:18,875 --> 00:51:20,500
for everything.

1203
00:51:20,583 --> 00:51:22,625
Thank you for saving me!

1204
00:51:42,666 --> 00:51:46,291
♪ My time is spinning around ♪

1205
00:51:46,375 --> 00:51:50,416
♪ Your deep black eyes ♪

1206
00:51:50,500 --> 00:51:54,208
♪ I forgot what time it is ♪

1207
00:51:54,291 --> 00:51:58,750
♪ And our memories are gone? ♪

1208
00:51:58,833 --> 00:52:00,833
[singing in Japanese]

1209
00:52:22,625 --> 00:52:23,833
♪ I wish you were here ♪

1210
00:52:23,916 --> 00:52:26,291
♪ Oh, never close your eyes ♪

1211
00:52:26,375 --> 00:52:28,458
♪ Searching for a true fate ♪

1212
00:52:28,541 --> 00:52:30,291
[singing in Japanese]

1213
00:52:38,333 --> 00:52:39,500
♪ "Restart" ♪

1214
00:52:39,583 --> 00:52:43,833
♪ So let us try again
from the very first time ♪

1215
00:52:43,916 --> 00:52:45,916
[singing in Japanese]

1216
00:52:52,833 --> 00:52:57,791
♪ For now, I'll see you off ♪

1217
00:52:59,625 --> 00:53:02,875
♪ And we'll die
waiting for a new day ♪

1218
00:53:02,958 --> 00:53:04,375
[singing in Japanese]

1219
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:10,666
♪ And we'll start
waiting for a new day ♪

1220
00:53:10,750 --> 00:53:11,916
[singing in Japanese]

1221
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:17,625
♪ Oh, please don't let me die ♪

1222
00:53:18,625 --> 00:53:20,625
[singing in Japanese]

1223
00:53:48,666 --> 00:53:51,458
[wind blowing]

1224
00:53:51,541 --> 00:53:53,458
[rumbling]

1225
00:53:55,583 --> 00:53:57,333
[carriages rattling]

1226
00:54:23,458 --> 00:54:23,500
[Emilia chuckles]

1227
00:54:25,791 --> 00:54:26,958
[Subaru gasps]

1228
00:54:29,125 --> 00:54:29,750
Hey, Petra...

1229
00:54:29,833 --> 00:54:32,291
aren't you a little close?

1230
00:54:32,375 --> 00:54:34,166
- Yeah, maybe, but she
had you all to herself earlier,

1231
00:54:34,250 --> 00:54:37,166
and I don't think that's fair.
It's my turn.

1232
00:54:37,250 --> 00:54:41,000
- Listen, I think you've
got this all wrong, Petra.

1233
00:54:41,083 --> 00:54:42,625
Subaru and I were just--

1234
00:54:42,708 --> 00:54:44,833
Uh, we had important things
to talk about.

1235
00:54:44,916 --> 00:54:46,666
- [groans]

1236
00:54:46,750 --> 00:54:47,500
No matter what it takes,

1237
00:54:47,583 --> 00:54:49,750
I'm not gonna lose to you.
Understand me?

1238
00:54:49,833 --> 00:54:50,958
- [gasps]

1239
00:54:51,041 --> 00:54:52,291
- Take it easy, Mili.

1240
00:54:52,375 --> 00:54:54,625
She's only a kid.
Just forget about it.

1241
00:54:54,708 --> 00:54:55,625
When they say outrageous things,

1242
00:54:55,708 --> 00:54:58,375
you've gotta smile
and laugh it off, you know?

1243
00:54:58,458 --> 00:54:59,500
- I can't do that!
- [gasps]

1244
00:54:59,583 --> 00:55:01,416
- Even if they're
only words from a child,

1245
00:55:01,500 --> 00:55:03,208
I refuse to take
such a lackadaisical attitude.

1246
00:55:03,291 --> 00:55:06,833
- Who uses words
like "lackadaisical" anymore?

1247
00:55:06,916 --> 00:55:08,375
- [growls]

1248
00:55:08,458 --> 00:55:10,041
You can't stop teasing me,
can you?

1249
00:55:10,125 --> 00:55:12,541
- I'm not a kid,
so don't talk to me like one!

1250
00:55:12,625 --> 00:55:14,541
- [both groan]
- Okay, okay, you two.

1251
00:55:14,625 --> 00:55:16,458
Take it easy.
Look, I'm sorry, Petra,

1252
00:55:16,541 --> 00:55:17,958
and I need to thank you.

1253
00:55:18,041 --> 00:55:20,041
You made a promise
not to leave Mili alone,

1254
00:55:20,125 --> 00:55:21,958
and you stuck to your word
through thick and thin,

1255
00:55:22,041 --> 00:55:24,375
so I really appreciate it.

1256
00:55:24,458 --> 00:55:26,125
Once things calm down,

1257
00:55:26,208 --> 00:55:29,000
there are actually
a lot of people I need to thank.

1258
00:55:29,791 --> 00:55:32,708
I'm grateful
to Crusch and her gang.

1259
00:55:32,791 --> 00:55:34,875
Anastasia and her people
helped a lot, too.

1260
00:55:34,958 --> 00:55:36,500
I hate to admit it,

1261
00:55:36,583 --> 00:55:39,041
but the same goes
for Julius and his crew.

1262
00:55:40,708 --> 00:55:43,750
And, you know,
I'm even indebted to Otto.

1263
00:55:43,833 --> 00:55:45,833
- Sorry. Were you trying
to say something to me?

1264
00:55:45,916 --> 00:55:48,625
- Nah, nothing in particular.

1265
00:55:48,708 --> 00:55:51,041
I'm just super grateful
to you, too, buddy!

1266
00:55:51,125 --> 00:55:54,500
- [gasps] My goodness.
What brought that on?

1267
00:55:54,583 --> 00:55:54,791
You're making me blush.

1268
00:55:54,875 --> 00:55:56,541
- Also...

1269
00:55:59,208 --> 00:55:59,500
[chuckles]

1270
00:56:01,666 --> 00:56:03,583
- What's wrong, Subaru?
- [gasps]

1271
00:56:03,666 --> 00:56:06,041
Oh! [laughs] Just, uh--

1272
00:56:06,125 --> 00:56:07,916
So listen, Mili.

1273
00:56:08,000 --> 00:56:08,958
[sighs]

1274
00:56:10,416 --> 00:56:12,083
There's something
extremely important

1275
00:56:12,166 --> 00:56:13,916
that I need to tell you.

1276
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:16,333
- Okay. What is it?

1277
00:56:16,416 --> 00:56:18,625
- This is gonna be
pretty hard for me to say,

1278
00:56:18,708 --> 00:56:19,458
but please hear me out.

1279
00:56:19,541 --> 00:56:22,125
And of course
it goes without saying

1280
00:56:22,208 --> 00:56:23,750
that I am completely prepared

1281
00:56:23,833 --> 00:56:26,416
to be knocked out by Ram
when I tell her!

1282
00:56:26,500 --> 00:56:29,000
But I wanted you
to hear it first.

1283
00:56:29,083 --> 00:56:30,041
- [grunts]

1284
00:56:32,041 --> 00:56:35,791
- This is--
This is actually about Rem.

1285
00:56:35,875 --> 00:56:38,125
She--She said that, uh...

1286
00:56:38,208 --> 00:56:39,291
<i>- And you'll still</i>
<i>keep me by your side,</i>

1287
00:56:39,375 --> 00:56:42,750
<i>no matter where you go</i>
<i>from now on?</i>

1288
00:56:42,833 --> 00:56:45,750
- S-So you see
what I'm getting at, right?

1289
00:56:45,833 --> 00:56:48,083
I mean, well, Rem said

1290
00:56:48,166 --> 00:56:50,750
some really nice things
to me, and, uh...

1291
00:56:50,833 --> 00:56:52,916
- Easy, Subaru. Just calm down.

1292
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:54,875
Now, I'm not exactly sure
what you're trying to say to me,

1293
00:56:54,958 --> 00:56:57,666
but I can tell it means a lot

1294
00:56:57,750 --> 00:56:59,125
and you're trying your hardest
to say it, okay?

1295
00:56:59,208 --> 00:57:02,833
Just take it slow,
like a good boy.

1296
00:57:02,916 --> 00:57:05,958
- "Like a good boy," huh?
Not exactly encouraging.

1297
00:57:06,041 --> 00:57:07,666
But all right. Here goes.

1298
00:57:07,750 --> 00:57:08,875
[grunts]

1299
00:57:08,958 --> 00:57:10,000
Time for me to man up,

1300
00:57:10,083 --> 00:57:12,750
come right out, and say it!

1301
00:57:12,833 --> 00:57:14,125
You see...

1302
00:57:14,208 --> 00:57:15,958
the thing is,
Rem said that she loves me,

1303
00:57:16,041 --> 00:57:18,041
and she meant it in the same way
I told you that I love you!

1304
00:57:18,125 --> 00:57:19,916
All right, there! I said it!

1305
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:22,250
[steeds' footsteps rumbling]

1306
00:57:22,333 --> 00:57:25,166
[gasping]

1307
00:57:25,250 --> 00:57:27,250
[carriages rattling]

1308
00:57:31,875 --> 00:57:33,666
- Subaru.

1309
00:57:33,750 --> 00:57:35,083
- Yes?

1310
00:57:38,041 --> 00:57:39,541
- I'm confused.

1311
00:57:42,125 --> 00:57:44,041
Who is Rem?

1312
00:57:44,125 --> 00:57:45,041
- [gasps]

1313
00:57:46,125 --> 00:57:47,041
[shudders]

